CHECK:ALLOC_SIZEOF_STRUCT: Prefer kzalloc(sizeof(*ir)...) over kzalloc(sizeof(struct irctl)...)
#114: FILE: drivers/lirc_igorplugusb/lirc_igorplugusb.c:433:
+	ir = kzalloc(sizeof(struct irctl), GFP_KERNEL);

The allocation style is bad.  In general for family of
allocation functions using sizeof() to get memory size,
constructs like::

  p = alloc(sizeof(struct foo), ...)

should be::

  p = alloc(sizeof(*p), ...)

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#allocating-memory

CHECK:ALLOC_SIZEOF_STRUCT: Prefer kzalloc(sizeof(*plugin)...) over kzalloc(sizeof(struct lirc_plugin)...)
#118: FILE: drivers/lirc_igorplugusb/lirc_igorplugusb.c:437:
+	plugin = kzalloc(sizeof(struct lirc_plugin), GFP_KERNEL);

